<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-09T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="343" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d343">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/1171: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-09T20:00:00-04:00">September 9, 1937—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>335. Reference Department’s 250, August 20, 6 p.m.,<note n="14" xml:id="d343fn14">Not printed.</note> regarding accommodation for
                            British refugees at Manila. Department has received an <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> from the British Embassy which states in
                            substance that His Majesty’s Government in the United Kingdom desire to
                            assure the United States Government that funds will be made available
                            for expenses that may be incurred in the Philippines as a result of the
                            reception there of British refugees.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>